											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/adrienne-mason/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Adrienne Mason writes about science and history for both adults and children. Her most recent book is <em>Whales to the Rescue: How Whales Help Engineer the Planet</em>. She helped launch <em>Hakai Magazine</em> and was its managing editor for eight and a half years. Previously, she was the managing editor of the children's science magazine <em>KNOW</em>. Photograph by Patrice Hansen</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/mason_head_shot-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="writer and editor Adrienne Mason" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/mason_head_shot-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/mason_head_shot-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/mason_head_shot-2048x2048.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/mason_head_shot-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/mason_head_shot-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/mason_head_shot-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/mason_head_shot-1200x1200.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
											</div>
											</a>
																															</section>
